The Supreme Court on Monday suspended the hearing of the appeals of Governors Aminu Tambuwal of Sokoto, Abdullahi Ganduje of Kano States. Other governors, whose appeals were affected are Emeka Ihedioha (Imo), Bala Mohammed (Bauchi), Simon Lalong (Plateau), and Samuel Ortom (Benue). The hearings were suspended over rowdiness in the court. The Chief Justice of Nigeria, Justice Tanko Muhammad, gave the order for the suspension of the appeals’ hearing.  Details shortly…